cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with graph problems and uses techniques from discrete mathematics, such as dynamic programming and counting equivalence classes. Therefore, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category. The paper also involves computational complexity, as it discusses upper and lower bounds on the size of graphs, so cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also likely categories. The paper deals with planar graphs and pathwidth, so cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is another possible category. Finally, the paper involves graph theory and combinatorics, so cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a less likely but still possible category.
